arch:property.oc:show_val: Main construction of the Bath Complex.

Locus 71 is the extant floor of the colonnaded corridor, located to the north of the stairway (Locus 48). The floor is made of sandstone ashlars in four rows, abutting the stairway. The pavers are dry-laid, with some evidence of a simple leveling course below it. The floor is phased to the main construction of the Bath Complex, Stage 2.
Floor of the colonnaded corridor north of the stairway

Phase VI: Late Nabataean pre CE 106 minor collapses and repairs. Probable early collapse of the Baroque Room and damage occurs in both the Anteroom and Shrine Room. The tabun in Room A is used to store CE 1st c. Nabataean fine wares. East 'Cistern" used as a dump. Bath Complex built.
3.20 m north south -by- 3.40 m east west.
